<h1 id="create-or-open-a-lesson" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#create-or-open-a-lesson">¶</a> Create or Open a Lesson</h1>
<h2 id="contents" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#contents">¶</a> Contents</h2>
<ol>
<li>Overview</li>
<li>Add a  New Lesson</li>
<li>Create Content in New Lesson</li>
<li>Open an Existing Lesson</li>
</ol>
<h1 id="h-1-overview" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-1-overview">¶</a> 1. Overview</h1>
<p>Creating a new lesson or finding an existing one in ANVILL is quick &amp; simple. Once created, all lessons get stored on one, easy-to-find page. There, you can also find ANVILL Lessons others have shared with you. Read below to learn what you need to know to get started!</p>
<p>Once you&apos;ve set-up your first lesson and started working on it, these additional ANVILL Wiki Help Desk pages may be of help:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="sharelesson" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Share Your Lesson</a></li>
<li><a href="organizelesson" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Organize your Lesson Layout</a></li>
<li><a href="lessonoutcomes" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">See Reports on Lesson Outcomes</a><br>
<em>Note:</em> Reports available for particular activities you&apos;ve created, by individual students (&quot;users&quot;), or as a general overview.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id="h-2-add-a-new-lesson" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-2-add-a-new-lesson">¶</a> 2. Add a New Lesson</h1>
<p><img src="../dashboard2.png" alt="dashboard2.png" height="200" class="align-right"></p>
<ol>
<li>Log in to ANVILL.</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://anvill.uoregon.edu/" class="is-external-link">Click here to open the ANVILL Login page</a>.<br>
 </li>
</ul>
<ol start="2">
<li>When you log in, your ANVILL &quot;Dashboard&quot; will open.</li>
<li>Click or tap on &quot;+ Lesson&quot; from the Dashboard.  A &quot;Create a New Lesson&quot; window will open!<br>
 <br>
<img src="../create_2.png" alt="create_2.png" height="250" class="align-center"></li>
<li>Give your new lesson a title.</li>
<li>Click or tap on &quot;Create&quot;. If you&apos;re using the Mobile App and don&apos;t see the &quot;Create&quot; button on your screen, simply scroll down a little.</li>
<li>Your new lesson page will now open.</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="../lesson_created.png" alt="lesson_created.png" height="600"></p>
<p>Note:<br>
If you want <strong><big>to start adding content and designing your lesson</big></strong><big> immediately, <strong>see Section 2 below</strong></big> to get started!</p>
<p>(Section 2 also includes information on popular ANVILL content types &amp; links to ANVILL Wiki Help Desk pages on using them.)</p>
<h1 id="h-3-create-content-in-a-new-lesson" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-3-create-content-in-a-new-lesson">¶</a> 3. Create Content in a New Lesson</h1>
<p><big><em><strong>Suggestions on how to start building your lesson:</strong></em></big></p>
<h2 id="h-31-add-your-first-content" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-31-add-your-first-content">¶</a> 3.1 <strong>Add Your First Content</strong>:</h2>
<ol>
<li>Click on &quot;+ Add Content&quot; at the top of your lesson page.</li>
<li>An &quot;Add Content&quot; menu pop will open containing all of your content options.</li>
<li>Find the content you want to add then  click on it.</li>
</ol>
<p><big><strong>Examples of Popular Content in ANVILL:</strong></big></p>
<p>Click on the below links to learn more about individual content and adding it to your lesson.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="../e/en/voiceboard" class="is-system-link">Voiceboard</a>: Design interactive speaking and discussion lessons with</li>
<li><a href="interactivebook" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Interactive Book</a><br>
<a href="coursepresentation" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Interactive Course Presentation</a>;<br>
<a href="interactivevideo" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Interactive Video</a><br>
Three options to increase engagement and comprehension with dynamic content. Each option allows you to add almost all other available ANVILL content as an interaction.</li>
<li><a href="../e/en/column" class="is-system-link">Column</a><br>
Layout tool and organizational container to organize and scaffold multiple ANVILL content and activities in one place on your lesson</li>
<li><a href="https://localhost/en/text" class="is-internal-link is-invalid-page">Text</a><br>
Straightforward way to publish written content in lesson (e.g. reference lists, instructions, background info, etc).</li>
<li><a href="dictation" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Dictation</a><br>
Record listening tasks.</li>
<li><a href="speakthewords" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Speak the Words</a> activities<br>
Learners can practice pronunciation using speech recognition software</li>
<li><a href="quiz" class="is-internal-link is-valid-page">Quiz Question Sets</a><br>
Add one ore more questions &amp; question types (e.g. Fill-in-the-Blank, Multiple Choice, True/False, Drag &amp; Drop, Essay) in a single quiz format.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="h-32-customize-lesson-header" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-32-customize-lesson-header">¶</a> 3.2 Customize Lesson Header</h2>
<p><strong>Customize Lesson Header:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Click on the camera icon in the upper left corner of your lesson header.</li>
<li>Select &quot;Choose Background Color&quot; or &apos;Upload Image&quot; in the drop-down menu.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="h-33-rename-your-lesson" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-33-rename-your-lesson">¶</a> 3.3 <strong>Rename Your Lesson:</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Click on the pencil icon in the bottom right corner of your header.</li>
<li>Type over the original title.</li>
<li>To save your work &amp; exit, click on the check mark icon in the bottom right of header.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id="h-4-open-an-existing-lesson" class="toc-header"><a class="toc-anchor" href="createlesson#h-4-open-an-existing-lesson">¶</a> 4. Open an Existing Lesson</h1>
<p>All lessons you create and save will automatically be stored on a single, easy-to-locate page in your ANVILL account. This &quot;Lesson Library&quot; makes it easy to access any current or past lesson of yours.</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://anvill.uoregon.edu/" class="is-external-link">Login</a> to ANVILL.</li>
<li>Click on the &quot;hamburger menu&quot;   <img src="../screen_shot_2020-05-17_at_12.38.57_pm.png" alt="screen_shot_2020-05-17_at_12.38.57_pm.png" height="20"> in the top left corner.</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="../hamburger_menu.png" alt="hamburger_menu.png" height="125"></p>
<p><img src="../lessons_in_menu.png" alt="lessons_in_menu.png" height="200" class="align-right"><br>
3. Select &apos;Lessons&apos; in the side-bar menu to open <strong>your ANVILL &quot;Lessons&quot; library.</strong></p>
<p>Note: <em>All</em> of your lessons &amp; shared lessons are stored on this page. Create a Lesson Folders to help organize.<br>
 <br>
4.  Find your lesson &amp; click on it to open.</p>
<ol start="5">
<li>You will now be automatically taken to your lesson.</li>
</ol>
